1 A BILL for an Act to amend and reenact subsection 20 of section 4.1-25-01 and sections
2 4.1-25-30, 4.1-25-31, 4.1-25-32, and 4.1-25-33 of the North Dakota Century Code, relating to
3 the definition of pasteurized milk ordinance and the federal pasteurized milk ordinance revision.
4 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
5 SECTION 1. AMENDMENT. Subsection 20 of section 4.1-25-01 of the North Dakota
6 Century Code is amended and reenacted as follows:
7 20. "Pasteurized milk ordinance" means the 20192023 revision of the Grade "A"
8 Pasteurized Ordinance issued by the United States food and drug administration and
9 by the United States department of agriculture's public health service.
10 SECTION 2. AMENDMENT. Section 4.1-25-30 of the North Dakota Century Code is
11 amended and reenacted as follows:
12 4.1-25-30. Standards for grade A milk and milk products - Adoption of rules.
13 Only grade A milk may be sold as a fluid beverage for human consumption. The minimum
14 standards for milk and milk products designated as grade A are the same as the minimum
15 requirements of the pasteurized milk ordinance which includes provisions from the "Grade A
16 Condensed and Dry Milk Products and Condensed and Dry Whey - Supplement 1 to the
17 Grade A PMO". The commissioner may adopt rules imposing other standards in the interest of
18 public safety, wholesomeness of product, consumer interest, sanitation, good supply, saleability,
19 and promotion of grade A milk and milk products.
20 SECTION 3. AMENDMENT. Section 4.1-25-31 of the North Dakota Century Code is
21 amended and reenacted as follows:
