1 4.1-25-31. State milk sanitation rating and sampling surveillance officer - Duties -
2 Guidelines.
3 The state milk sanitation rating and sampling surveillance officer is responsible for the rating
4 and certification of milk and dairy products. The rating and certification of milk and dairy
5 products must be in accordance with the procedures outlined in the public health service food
6 and drug administration publication entitled "Methods of Making Sanitation Ratings of Milk
7 Shippers - 2019and the Certifications/Listings of Single-Service Containers and/or Closures for
8 Milk and/or Milk Products Manufacturers 2023 Revision, Edition" and the sampling of milk and
9 dairy products must be in accordance with the guidelines in the Standard Methods.
10 SECTION 4. AMENDMENT. Section 4.1-25-32 of the North Dakota Century Code is
11 amended and reenacted as follows:
12 4.1-25-32. Milk laboratory evaluations officer - Duties - Guidelines.
13 The milk laboratory evaluations officer is responsible for the certification and evaluation of
14 milk and dairy products laboratories within the state. Evaluations and certification of milk
15 laboratories must be made in accordance with the Standard Methods and the procedures
16 outlined in the public health service food and drug administration publication entitled "Evaluation
17 of Milk Laboratories - 20192023 Edition".
18 SECTION 5. AMENDMENT. Section 4.1-25-33 of the North Dakota Century Code is
19 amended and reenacted as follows:
20 4.1-25-33. Grade A pasteurized milk ordinance.
21 Dairy producers, processors, and manufacturers shall comply with the pasteurized milk
22 ordinance and follow the standards set by the "Procedures Governing the Cooperative
23 State-Public Health Service Food and Drug Administration Program of the National Conference
24 on Interstate Milk Shipments, 20192023 Revision".
